.TH "tpm_calc_ordinal_duration" 9 "tpm_calc_ordinal_duration" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_calc_ordinal_duration \- calculate the maximum command duration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" tpm_calc_ordinal_duration
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u32 ordinal "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
TPM chip to use.
.IP "ordinal" 12
TPM command ordinal.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function returns the maximum amount of time the chip could take
to return the result for a particular ordinal in jiffies.
.SH "RETURN"
A maximal duration time for an ordinal in jiffies.
